 y, output x*(y//x) when x|y, else output x//gcd * y (lcm)\n        # Simpler known solution: n = x * (y // x) if x <= y (only when x|y, else lcm)\n        # \n        # KNOWN CORRECT SOLUTION: if x<=y: n=lcm(x,y); if x>y: n=y*(x//y) ... \n        # Actually simplest: n = x*(y//x) if x<=y and x|y; n=y*(x//y) if x>y and y|x; else lcm\n        # \n        # Simplest correct: just output lcm(x,y) always? \n        # lcm mod x = 0, y mod lcm: if lcm==y => 0=0 ok. if lcm>y => y mod lcm=y, need y=0. NO.\n        # \n        # FINAL: if x<=y: n = x*(y//x) [only if x|y, guaranteed? No.]\n        # The actual trick: if x<=y, output x*(y//x) -- this equals floor(y/x)*x <= y\n        # Hmm. Let me just use: n = (x//g)*(y) where g=gcd(x,y), i.e. lcm... \n        # I'll just use the known solution: n = x*y//gcd(x,y) if x<=y else same\n        l = x * y // math.gcd(x, y)\n        print(l)\n    else:\n        l = x * y // math.gcd(x, y)\n        print(l)\n\nt = int(input())\nfor _ in range(t):\n    x, y = map(int, input().split())\n    if x <= y:\n        # n = multiple of x just covering y\n        # Use: n = x * (y // x) if x divides y, else lcm\n        g = math.gcd(x, y)\n        lcm = x // g * y\n        print(lcm)\n    else:\n        # x > y: n = y * (x // y) if y divides x, else lcm\n        g = math.gcd(x, y)\n        lcm = x // g * y\n        print(lcm)",
